# 🧪 Plan Your Experiments

**Plan your experiment before you book the microscope.** Careful experimental design is crucial for acquiring quantitative, unbiased, and reproducible imaging data.

## 📖 Essential Reading
Before starting your imaging project, we highly recommend reviewing these foundational guides:

* [Accuracy and precision in quantitative fluorescence microscopy – A foundational guide to collecting quantitative data](https://rupress.org/jcb/article/185/7/1135/35453/Accuracy-and-precision-in-quantitative)
* [Designing a rigorous microscopy experiment – Validating methods and avoiding bias](https://rupress.org/jcb/article/218/5/1452/120908/Designing-a-rigorous-microscopy-experiment)
* [Believing is seeing – The deceptive influence of bias in quantitative microscopy](https://journals.biologists.com/jcs/article/137/1/jcs261567/341218/Believing-is-seeing-the-deceptive-influence-of)

