## 🤖 AI-Assisted Microscope Selection

Choosing the right microscope for your specific biological question can be challenging. Because our facility maintains a highly structured database, you can use AI assistants (like ChatGPT, Claude, or Copilot) to recommend the best system for your needs based on our *actual* inventory!

### Step 1: Download our Facility Database
Download the tailored, AI-ready snapshot of our active microscope inventory. This file includes current hardware capabilities and live instrument health statuses.

[⬇️ Download `llm_inventory.json`](assets/llm_inventory.json){: download="llm_inventory.json" .md-button .md-button--primary style="margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px;" }

### Step 2: Open your preferred AI Assistant
Go to your preferred AI tool (e.g., ChatGPT, Claude) and ensure it supports file uploads.

### Step 3: Upload the file and use this prompt
Upload the `llm_inventory.json` file you just downloaded. Then, copy and paste the prompt below, filling in the bracketed `[ ]` information with your specific experimental details:

<div class="admonition abstract">
  <p class="admonition-title">Copy and paste this into the AI:</p>
  <p>I have attached a JSON file containing the exact inventory and current health status of microscopes in my core facility. I need to plan an imaging experiment. Here is a description of my experiment:</p>
  <p><strong>[Describe your biological sample, what you are trying to observe, and any specific needs you have. For example: Do you need live-cell incubation? High-speed volumetric imaging? Deep tissue penetration? If you know the dyes or fluorophores you want to use, list them here. If not, just describe the colors or structures you are targeting.]</strong></p>
  <p>Based ONLY on the active microscopes available in the attached file, which 1 or 2 systems would you recommend and why? Please take into account their current health status (do not recommend offline systems). Mention the specific modality, objective, and light sources that make your recommended system a good fit.</p>
</div>

